annotationA: 60S ribosomal protein L8; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: regulation of cell size; insulin receptor signaling pathway; mitotic spindle elongation; translation; compound eye development; centrosome duplication; mitotic spindle organization
annotationB: Translationally controlled tumor protein (Tctp) belongs to the TCTP family. It interacts with the GTPase Rheb to regulate organ growth. Tctp is required for DNA damage response and genome stability
